transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. This is Olivia speaking. Who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, hi. My name is Ruben Munoz, last name is M-U-N-O-Z, and I just got an order in yesterday of Cyndamifil, which is generic for Viagra.

Speaker 1: Okay, how do I stop these from coming? Because I got an order recently sent to me,

Speaker 2: and I thought I had contacted them and told them to stop sending them, and I just got one in the mail yesterday.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can look into that for you. So what is the phone number that's going to be associated with your prescription for me to look into?

Speaker 2: Okay, it's 818-370-1742.

Speaker 1: Okay, there you are, Ruben. And what is your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 10-31-1958.

Speaker 1: Great. And you're located in Montrose, California?

Speaker 2: Correct.

Speaker 1: Amazing. Yeah, so I do see you here. All right.

Speaker 2: Just how do I stop having you send me anymore?

Speaker 1: Yeah, if you don't want to receive regular refills with your prescription, you certainly don't have to.

Speaker 2: You always have the option with your prescription to place it on hold for up to six months at a time,

Speaker 1: just because six months is when the prescription would expire if we didn't refill it.

Speaker 2: So the way that would work is if you did want to order within the next six months or before July 28th of this year, you could.

Speaker 1: You just have to give us a call to place the order yourself.

Speaker 2: Okay. But I don't need any more sent out to me.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, no, I completely understand that.

Speaker 2: But, yeah, if you, you know, do want to keep access to the script, you do have that option that if you just leave it on hold.

Speaker 1: If you do want to call back and order with it, you can, as opposed to having to restart it and having to pay a separate –

Speaker 2: we have a new policy that you'd have to pay a separate doctor fee.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: So put it on hold, and I will contact you when I need some more.

Speaker 2: Okay, great. Yeah. Well, thank you so much, Ruben.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: I hope you have a great day, and if you need anything before the end of July, just let us know.

Speaker 1: Okay. All right. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you. Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye.
